  "prompt": "What does Hillary Clinton think of high-skill immigration?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has generally been supportive of high-skill immigration. Throughout her political career, she has advocated for reforms that make it easier for skilled immigrants to work in the United States. During her 2016 presidential campaign, she called for expanding the number of visas for skilled workers and emphasized the importance of attracting talent to foster innovation and economic growth. Her stance has been that high-skill immigrants contribute significantly to the U.S. economy and help maintain its competitive edge globally. However, for her most current views, it would be best to refer to her recent statements or writings.",
